+# Exploration 001 Report
+
+## Goal
+
+Identify a very small candidate family of exact phase/coherence objects built
+from exact Fourier or helical interaction data, then classify each candidate as
+`intrinsic`, `canonically representable but non-intrinsic`, or `inadmissible`
+under an explicit equivalence and admissibility test.
+
+## Method
+
+- Start from local mission context and prior Atlas/Navier-Stokes notes.
+- Extract the allowed quotient operations and admissibility requirements.
+- Propose at most three raw candidate object classes with formula-level
+  definitions that avoid desired-channel labels, packet sheets, and frozen
+  transfer annotations.
+- Test each candidate against the extracted equivalence relation.
+
+## Working Notes
+
+### Initial skeleton
+
+This report is being written incrementally. Findings, failed attempts, and
+intermediate interpretations will be appended below as the exploration
+proceeds.
+
+## Findings
+
+### Pending
+
+Context gathering in progress.
+
+## Dead Ends / Rejections
+
+None yet.
+
+## Provisional Conclusion
+
+Pending.

