missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/judgments/chain-01.md:29:The attacker is right that the original audit lumps together different kinds of transformations that should not be judged by the same standard. True exact symmetries, canonical representation choices, and substantively different modeling decisions are not interchangeable. A candidate should usually be invariant under the first category, but dependence on a fixed canonical presentation is not automatically fatal.
