./missions/navier-stokes/library-inbox/vasseur-2007-proof-architecture.md:162:- **P_k^1 is harmonic:** −ΔP_k^1 = 0 in [T_{k−1},1]×B_{k−2/3}. This is the "non-local" part carrying global pressure information. It is controlled by Lemma 7 using the *global* ||P||_{L^p(L¹)} norm:
./missions/navier-stokes/library-inbox/vasseur-2007-proof-architecture.md:164:    ||P_k^1||_{L^p(T_{k−1},1; L∞(B_{k−1/3}))} ≤ C·2^{12k}·(||P||_{L^p(L¹)} + ||u||²_{L∞(L²)})
