| `Template-Defect Near-Closure` | `stable after canonicalization` | the defect observable depends on one frozen packet sheet, but not on post hoc packet rewrites or threshold retuning |
| `Windowed Spectator-Leakage Budget` | `stable after canonicalization` | the only serious robustness burden is whether the frozen spectator partition and normalization are canonical enough |
| `Delayed-Threshold Itinerary` | `use-case-limited but honest` | the candidate is genuinely finite-window and sheet-dependent, but those limits were frozen up front rather than chosen after outcomes |

